 THE PILOT ATTEMPTED TO MAKE AN AERO-TOW TAKEOFF IN THE FUSELAGE 
WHEEL LANDING GEAR EQUIPPED GLIDER WITH THE LEFT WING SKID ON THE 
RUNWAY.  THE AIRCRAFT DRIFTED LEFT AT THE BEGINNING OF THE TAKEOFF ROLL AND 
THE LEFT WING IMPACTED A TAXIWAY SIGN BESIDE THE RUNWAY WHEN THE AIRCRAFT 
REACHED ABOUT 5 MPH. 
 THE PROPER ALIGNMENT WAS NOT MAINTAINED BY THE PILOT.  A FACTOR 
RELATING TO THE ACCIDENT WAS THE SIGN LOCATED BESIDE THE RUNWAY. 
